A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Chapter 1 of Title 50 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
2 general provisions regarding state government, so as to designate the City of Incheon, South
3 Korea as the sister city-state of the State of Georgia; to provide legislative findings and
4 declarations; to provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
5 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
6 SECTION 1.
7 The General Assembly finds and declares as follows:
8 (1) As of February 2020, Incheon was home to approximately 3 million residents,
9 making it the third most populous city in South Korea, following Seoul and Busan;
10 (2) Incheon is a major port city, serving as a crucial hub for international trade and
11 maritime commerce as well as the home to Incheon International Airport, one of the
12 busiest and most advanced airports in the world;
13 (3) Incheon has been designated as an "English City" and has implemented the "Incheon
14 Free English Zone" initiative, emphasizing global communication and education;
15 (4) Incheon has established sister city-state relationships with 39 cities around the world;
